Pinus roxburghii

   [8653.jpg]
    Authority   Sarg.
      Family    Pinopsida:Pinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names chir pine
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8653

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Webb D 1984 pp 230 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   Sims D (pers. comm.)
   Troup R 1921 pp 1036
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 424 [USE]
   INSPIRE species 147 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, USE]
   KILLING T
   Frost resistant.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Rather slow growing perennial evergreen tree, that can be grown in a
   90-160 years rotation for hardwood.
   COMMON NAMES
   Chir pine, Long-leaved pine, Longifolia pine, Chil, Shti, Sarol, Sirli,
   Dhup.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: P. longifolia. In the Himalayan, Chir pine can be
   found at elevations from 500 to 2500 m. The latitudinal range of
   natural occurrence is 26-35Â°N. The tree can reach a height of 30-60 m.
   The tree is drought hardy and fire resistant. Annual wood production
   potential is 7-14 m3/ha.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
